mdmInstalledRacks.name: mdmInstalledRacks
mdmInstalledRacks.description: This is the number of currently installed modem racks.

mdmInstalledModems.name: mdmInstalledModems
mdmInstalledModems.description: This is the number of currently installed modems

mdmLoopModeTraps.name: mdmLoopModeTraps
mdmLoopModeTraps.description: This enables or disables traps generated by a Loop Mode status change at any local modem port of one of the installed modems (values: disable, enable).

mdmCurrentDate.name: mdmCurrentDate
mdmCurrentDate.description: This indicate the current date as 'mm/dd/yy'. The date will be used for local management.

mdmCurrentTime.name: mdmCurrentTime
mdmCurrentTime.description: This indicate the current time as 'hh:mm:ss'. The time will be used for local management.

mdmRackTable.name: mdmRackTable
mdmRackTable.description: Table which contains information about the installed racks.

rackRack.name: rackRack
rackRack.description: The index of this particular modem rack in the stack. The index of the rack which contains the agent should have the number 1.

rackType.name: rackType
rackType.description: This entry shows the type number of the rack.

rackDescription.name: rackDescription
rackDescription.description: A verbal description of the modem rack.

rackModemSlots.name: rackModemSlots
rackModemSlots.description: This entry shows the number of slots for modem cards in the rack.

rackModems.name: rackModems
rackModems.description: This entry shows the number of modems currently installed in the rack.

rackPowerSupplySlots.name: rackPowerSupplySlots
rackPowerSupplySlots.description: This entry shows the number of slots for power supplies in the rack.

rackPowerSupplies.name: rackPowerSupplies
rackPowerSupplies.description: This entry shows the number of power supplies currently installed in the rack.

mdmModemTable.name: mdmModemTable
mdmModemTable.description: Table which contains general information about the installed modems.

mdmRack.name: mdmRack
mdmRack.description: The index of the rack where the modem is installed.

mdmModem.name: mdmModem
mdmModem.description: The index of this particular modem in the rack. The value corresponds with the slot where the modem is inserted.

mdmDescription.name: mdmDescription
mdmDescription.description: A verbal description of the modem.

mdmUserName.name: mdmUserName
mdmUserName.description: A verbal description of the modem which can be changed by the manager.

mdmSelfTest.name: mdmSelfTest
mdmSelfTest.description: This entry enables the execution of a selftest. Write requests with values other than 'start' or 'cancel' will be rejected. The result will be found in mdmSelfTestResult.

mdmSelfTestResult.name: mdmSelfTestResult
mdmSelfTestResult.description: This entry shows the result status of the last modem-dependent self test. After start, the status may change to 'running' before the first error that occured is displayed. If no error was detected the status changes to 'ok'.

mdmRemoteAccessStatus.name: mdmRemoteAccessStatus
mdmRemoteAccessStatus.description: This entry shows the access status to the remote counterpart of the modem. The standard value depends on the device. Some remote modems are always accessible, others are not accessible or can be switched to both modes (see 'mdmForcedRemoteAccess' in the specific modem MIB).

mdmInterfacePorts.name: mdmInterfacePorts
mdmInterfacePorts.description: This entry indicates the number of interface ports of the modem. An interface port connects an external device.

mdmLinePorts.name: mdmLinePorts
mdmLinePorts.description: This entry indicates the number of line ports of the modem. A line port connects a remote modem.

mdmVerInfoTable.name: mdmVerInfoTable
mdmVerInfoTable.description: Table which contains information about the installed modems' versions.

viRack.name: viRack
viRack.description: The index of the rack where the modem is installed.

viModem.name: viModem
viModem.description: The index of this particular modem in the rack. The value corresponds with the slot where the modem is inserted.

viType.name: viType
viType.description: This entry indicates the type of the modem.

viFirmwVer.name: viFirmwVer
viFirmwVer.description: This entry indicates the firmware revision of the modem.

viUnitRel.name: viUnitRel
viUnitRel.description: This entry indicates the hardware version and revision of the modem.

viArtNo.name: viArtNo
viArtNo.description: This entry indicates the article number of the modem.

viSerialNumber.name: viSerialNumber
viSerialNumber.description: This entry indicates the serial number of the modem.

mdmPortTable.name: mdmPortTable
mdmPortTable.description: Table which contains information about all ports.

portRack.name: portRack
portRack.description: The index of the rack where the modem to which this port belongs is installed.

portModem.name: portModem
portModem.description: The index of the modem to which this port belongs.

portType.name: portType
portType.description: This entry indicates the type of the port.

portInterfaceType.name: portInterfaceType
portInterfaceType.description: This entry indicates the type of interface of the port.

portConnector.name: portConnector
portConnector.description: This entry indicates the connector type of the port.

portLoopMode.name: portLoopMode
portLoopMode.description: This entry indicates the loop mode of the port.

mdmPortSignalTable.name: mdmPortSignalTable
mdmPortSignalTable.description: Table which contains information about all port status signals.

psignalRack.name: psignalRack
psignalRack.description: The index of the rack where the modem is installed to which the port belongs that provides the signal.

psignalModem.name: psignalModem
psignalModem.description: The index of the modem to which the port belongs that provides the signal.

psignalPort.name: psignalPort
psignalPort.description: The index of the port that provides the signal.

psignalType.name: psignalType
psignalType.description: This entry indicates the signal type.

psignalStatus.name: psignalStatus
psignalStatus.description: This entry indicates the current status of the signal.

psignalTrap.name: psignalTrap
psignalTrap.description: This enables or disables traps. If Trap is enabled each transition of the signal status may cause a trap portSignalStatusGood/portSignalStatusBad.

mdmBERTTable.name: mdmBERTTable
mdmBERTTable.description: Table which contains information about all performable bit error rate tests.

bertRack.name: bertRack
bertRack.description: The index of the rack where the modem is installed.

bertModem.name: bertModem
bertModem.description: The index of this particular modem in the rack. The value corresponds with the slot where the modem is inserted.

bertPort.name: bertPort
bertPort.description: The index of the port where the BER test will be performed. The modem can only perform one test at a time. The test can only be performed on a subset of ports, usually the line ports. Write requests with different port numbers will be rejected. Write requests with valid line port numbers will be rejected while the BER test is running.

bertBERTest.name: bertBERTest
bertBERTest.description: This entry enables the execution of a BER test. Write requests with values other than 'start' or 'stop' will be rejected.

bertStatus.name: bertStatus
bertStatus.description: This entry indicates the status of the BER test.

bertRunTime.name: bertRunTime
bertRunTime.description: This entry indicates the duration of the BER test in seconds.

bertInErrorTime.name: bertInErrorTime
bertInErrorTime.description: This entry shows the duration of erroneous test transmission in seconds.

bertErrorFreeTime.name: bertErrorFreeTime
bertErrorFreeTime.description: This entry shows the duration of error-free test transmission in seconds.

bertKbitsRecWrapped.name: bertKbitsRecWrapped
bertKbitsRecWrapped.description: This is the number the bertKbitsReceived counter has wrapped.

bertKbitsReceived.name: bertKbitsReceived
bertKbitsReceived.description: This entry indicates the number of Kbits received during the test. When the counter wraps the bertKbitRecWrapped increases by one.

bertErrors.name: bertErrors
bertErrors.description: This entry indicates the number of errors detected during the test.

bertSyncLosts.name: bertSyncLosts
bertSyncLosts.description: This entry indicates the number of pattern sync losts detected during the test.

bertSyncStatus.name: bertSyncStatus
bertSyncStatus.description: This entry indicates the current pattern sync status.

bertBitErrorRate.name: bertBitErrorRate
bertBitErrorRate.description: This entry indicates the bit error rate. It is provided as a string in the format 'd.ddE+/-dd'. Float scanf routines are capable of interpreting the string in the correct manner.

remModemTable.name: remModemTable
remModemTable.description: Table which contains general information about all counterparts of the installed modems.

rmdmRack.name: rmdmRack
rmdmRack.description: This entry indicates the index of the rack where the modem is installed that the remote modem is linked to.

rmdmModem.name: rmdmModem
rmdmModem.description: The index of the modem that the remote modem is linked to.

rmdmDescription.name: rmdmDescription
rmdmDescription.description: A verbal description of the remote modem.

rmdmUserName.name: rmdmUserName
rmdmUserName.description: A verbal description of the remote modem which can be changed by the manager.

rmdmSelfTest.name: rmdmSelfTest
rmdmSelfTest.description: This entry enables the execution of a selftest. Write requests with values other than 'start' or 'cancel' will be rejected. The result will be found in SelfTestResult.

rmdmSelfTestResult.name: rmdmSelfTestResult
rmdmSelfTestResult.description: This indicates the result status of the last modem-dependent self test. After start, the status may change to 'running' before the first error that occured displays. If no error was detected the status changes to 'ok'.

rmdmRemoteAccessStatus.name: rmdmRemoteAccessStatus
rmdmRemoteAccessStatus.description: This entry shows the access status of the modem. The standard value depends on the device. Some modems are always accessible, others are not accessible or can be switched to both modes (see 'mdmForcedRemoteAccess' in the specific modem MIB).

rmdmInterfacePorts.name: rmdmInterfacePorts
rmdmInterfacePorts.description: This entry indicates the number of interface ports of the remote modem. An interface port connects an external device.

rmdmLinePorts.name: rmdmLinePorts
rmdmLinePorts.description: This entry indicates the number of line ports of the modem. A line port connects the local counterpart of the remote modem.

remVerInfoTable.name: remVerInfoTable
remVerInfoTable.description: Table which contains information about the remote modems' versions.

rviRack.name: rviRack
rviRack.description: The index of the rack where the modem is installed that the remote modem is linked to.

rviModem.name: rviModem
rviModem.description: The index of the modem that the remote modem is linked to.

rviType.name: rviType
rviType.description: This entry indicates the type of the remote modem.

rviFirmwVer.name: rviFirmwVer
rviFirmwVer.description: This entry indicates the firmware revision of the remote modem.

rviUnitRel.name: rviUnitRel
rviUnitRel.description: This entry indicates the hardware version and revision of the remote modem.

rviArtNo.name: rviArtNo
rviArtNo.description: This entry indicates the article number of the remote modem.

rviSerialNumber.name: rviSerialNumber
rviSerialNumber.description: This entry indicates the serial number of the remote modem.

remPortTable.name: remPortTable
remPortTable.description: Table which contains information about all ports of the remote modem.

rportRack.name: rportRack
rportRack.description: The index of the rack where the local counterpart of the remote modem is installed to which this port belongs.

rportModem.name: rportModem
rportModem.description: The index of the local counterpart of the remote modem to which this port belongs.

rportType.name: rportType
rportType.description: This entry indicates the type of the port.

rportInterfaceType.name: rportInterfaceType
rportInterfaceType.description: This entry indicates the type of interface of the port.

rportConnector.name: rportConnector
rportConnector.description: This entry indicates the connector type of the port.

rportLoopMode.name: rportLoopMode
rportLoopMode.description: This entry indicates the loop mode of the port (remote, digital, line, off).

remPortSignalTable.name: remPortSignalTable
remPortSignalTable.description: Table which contains information about all port status signals.

rpsignalRack.name: rpsignalRack
rpsignalRack.description: The index of the rack where the local counterpart of the remote modem is installed.

rpsignalModem.name: rpsignalModem
rpsignalModem.description: The index of the local counterpart of the remote modem.

rpsignalPort.name: rpsignalPort
rpsignalPort.description: The index of the port at the remote modem that provides the signal.

rpsignalType.name: rpsignalType
rpsignalType.description: This entry indicates the signal type.

rpsignalStatus.name: rpsignalStatus
rpsignalStatus.description: This entry indicates the current status of the signal.

mdmIfType.name: mdmIfType
mdmIfType.description: This variable shows the agent's interface type.

mdmIfProtocol.name: mdmIfProtocol
mdmIfProtocol.description: This variable shows the agent's protocol type.

mdmIfDataRate.name: mdmIfDataRate
mdmIfDataRate.description: This variable shows the agent's data rate in bps.

mdmIfDialEnable.name: mdmIfDialEnable
mdmIfDialEnable.description: This variable enables the initialization of a dial modem in case of alarm. The following variables (5 to 10) are active only if this variable is enabled.

mdmIfInitString.name: mdmIfInitString
mdmIfInitString.description: This variable defines an init string which is generated in case of alarm to configure an external Hayes compatible modem.

mdmIfDialString.name: mdmIfDialString
mdmIfDialString.description: This variable defines a modem command which is generated in case of alarm to dial-up a remote NMS station. If the dial string is not defined neither the init string nor the dial string is generated.

mdmIfSendTTL.name: mdmIfSendTTL
mdmIfSendTTL.description: This variable defines the TTL (time to live) in seconds. After that time the generated traps will be deleted from the buffer. If the value is '0' the traps will remain in the buffer.

mdmIfDialTimeout.name: mdmIfDialTimeout
mdmIfDialTimeout.description: This variable defines a dial timeout for the modem in seconds.

mdmIfRedialPause.name: mdmIfRedialPause
mdmIfRedialPause.description: This variable defines the duration of a redial pause in seconds.

mdmIfIdlePeriodBeforeDisconnect.name: mdmIfIdlePeriodBeforeDisconnect
mdmIfIdlePeriodBeforeDisconnect.description: This variable defines the period of time before disconnecting in seconds. If the value is '0' the modem will remain connected.

rackAdded.name: rackAdded
rackAdded.description: This trap will be sent when a rack is added to the managed chassis. The rack index of the new rack is sent along with this trap.

rackRemoved.name: rackRemoved
rackRemoved.description: This trap will be sent when a rack is removed from the managed chassis. The rack index of the removed rack is sent along with this trap.

modemAdded.name: modemAdded
modemAdded.description: This trap will be sent when a modem is added. The rack number and the index of the new modem is sent along with this trap.

modemRemoved.name: modemRemoved
modemRemoved.description: This trap will be sent when a modem in one of the slots is removed. The rack number and the index of the removed modem is sent along with this trap.

portLoopEnabled.name: portLoopEnabled
portLoopEnabled.description: This trap will be sent when a modem in one of the slots enables a Loop. The rack number, index of the modem, and port number is sent along with this trap.

portLoopDisabled.name: portLoopDisabled
portLoopDisabled.description: This trap will be sent when a modem in one of the slots disables a Loop. The rack number, index of the modem, and port number is sent along with this trap.

portSignalStatusGood.name: portSignalStatusGood
portSignalStatusGood.description: This will be sent when a status signal of a modem port enters the 'good' status. The rack number, index of the modem, and port number is sent along with this trap.

portSignalStatusBad.name: portSignalStatusBad
portSignalStatusBad.description: This trap will be sent when a status signal of a modem port enters the 'bad' status. The rack number, index of the modem, and port number is sent along with this trap.

portBackupEnabled.name: portBackupEnabled
portBackupEnabled.description: This trap will be sent when a modem in one of the slots enters a backup status. The first port indicates the active data port, the second the inactive port. The rack number, index of the modem, and port number is sent along with this trap.

portBackupDisabled.name: portBackupDisabled
portBackupDisabled.description: This trap will be sent when a modem in one of the slots leaves a backup status. The first port indicates the active data port, the second the inactive port. The rack number, index of the modem, and port number is sent along with this trap.

portBackupAvailable.name: portBackupAvailable
portBackupAvailable.description: This trap will be sent when a second link can be used as backup. The rack number, index of the modem, and port number is sent along with this trap.

portBackupNotAvailable.name: portBackupNotAvailable
portBackupNotAvailable.description: This trap will be sent when there is no second link available as backup. The rack number, index of the modem, and port number is sent along with this trap.

portDataPortChanged.name: portDataPortChanged
portDataPortChanged.description: This trap will be sent when the line port used for data transmission is changed. The first port indicates the active data port, the second the inactive port. The rack number, index of the modem, and port number is sent along with this trap.
